to the editor thomas l friedman column aug 4 suggests that most americans care less about foreign affairs than about the economy the electorate is fickle even a 90 percent approval rating of president bush 's handling of the persian gulf war was n't enough to get him re elected gov george w bush 's campaign team understands this voter mentality the failed middle east peace talks coupled with leadership changes in syria and jordan demand that the next administration have a foreign policy a team to argue that governor bush has no reassuring economic wise men is off the mark one of mr bush 's top advisers is george p shultz who has a phd in economics from the massachusetts institute of technology and has held four cabinet positions the republicans are covering all of the bases james a paladino tampa fla aug 4 2000

